To avoid the per-agent loop in GDScript, we should perform the stride-12 buffer interleaving directly in Rust. This compiled implementation is highly optimized and runs in sub-millisecond time even at maximum agent capacity.

```rust
    fn get_agent_health_tint_buffer(&self) -> PackedFloat32Array {
        let snapshot_guard = match self.snapshot_buffer.try_read() {
            Ok(g) => g,
            Err(_) => return PackedFloat32Array::new(),
        };
        let health_guard = match self.agent_health_buffer.try_read() {
            Ok(g) => g,
            Err(_) => return PackedFloat32Array::new(),
        };

        let count = snapshot_guard.len() / 8;
        let mut tinted = Vec::with_capacity(count * 12);
        let health_len = health_guard.len();
        for i in 0..count {
            let src = i * 8;
            tinted.extend_from_slice(&snapshot_guard[src..src + 8]);
            let frac = if i < health_len {
                health_guard[i] as f32 / 255.0
            } else {
                1.0
            };
            tinted.push(frac);
            tinted.push(0.0);
            tinted.push(0.0);
            tinted.push(0.0);
        }
        PackedFloat32Array::from(tinted.as_slice())
    }
```

