### Critical Bug: One-Frame Camera Snap/Flicker on Resume

There is a discrepancy between the design specification and the implementation of the resume path. The spec states:
> *"resume must call a re-point-only path that reads position from the live World (§ Arch 1)."*

However, `resume_suspended_overworld` only calls `repoint_ffi_buffers`, which inserts the FFI-shared Arcs into the world but does **not** update their values with the player's (or vehicle's) current position from the resumed overworld. As a result, the FFI buffers (`self.player_position_buffer` and `self.vehicle_position_buffer`) will continue to hold the stale final positions from the interior world until the first tick of the resumed overworld runs. This causes a visible one-frame camera snap/flicker to the interior position on resume, violating **AC4**.

To fix this, we should query the live positions from the resumed world `w` and update the FFI buffers immediately during `resume_suspended_overworld`, matching the pattern used in `install_built_world` but reading from the live world instead of spawn constants.

```rust
                let player_seed_xy = {
                    let mut q = w.query::<(
                        &crate::components::WorldPosition,
                        &crate::components::Player,
                    )>();
                    q.iter(&w)
                        .next()
                        .map(|(p, _)| (p.x, p.y))
                        .unwrap_or((PLAYER_SPAWN_X, PLAYER_SPAWN_Y))
                };
                if let Ok(mut buf) = self.player_position_buffer.write() {
                    *buf = player_seed_xy;
                }
                let vehicle_seed_xyz = {
                    let handle_opt = {
                        let mut q = w.query::<(
                            &crate::components::VehicleHandle,
                            &crate::components::Vehicle,
                        )>();
                        q.iter(&w).next().map(|(h, _)| h.0)
                    };
                    handle_opt
                        .and_then(|handle| {
                            let rapier = w.get_resource::<crate::vehicle::RapierWorld>()?;
                            let body = rapier.bodies.get(handle)?;
                            let t = body.translation();
                            Some((t.x, t.y, t.z))
                        })
                        .unwrap_or((VEHICLE_SPAWN_X, VEHICLE_SPAWN_Y, VEHICLE_SPAWN_Z))
                };
                if let Ok(mut buf) = self.vehicle_position_buffer.write() {
                    *buf = (
                        vehicle_seed_xyz.0,
                        vehicle_seed_xyz.1,
                        vehicle_seed_xyz.2,
                        0.0,
                    );
                }
                self.world = Some(w);
                self.schedule = Some(build_sim_schedule());
```

