In `set_fixture`, the `pending_transition_fixtures` queue is only updated if `registry` is not empty. If a previous `set_fixture` call queued a non-empty registry, and a subsequent `set_fixture` call is made with an empty registry (i.e., a fixture with no transition targets), the old registry will persist in `pending_transition_fixtures`. When `ensure_initialized` is called, it will drain this stale registry and apply it to the new fixture.

To prevent stale transition targets from leaking across queued fixtures, `pending_transition_fixtures` should always be overwritten with the new `registry` (even if it is empty).

```rust
        match self.pending_transition_fixtures.try_write() {
            Ok(mut reg_buf) => *reg_buf = registry,
            Err(_) => {
                godot_error!(
                    "set_fixture: pending_transition_fixtures lock contended; whole queue \
                     rejected (main fixture NOT committed) to avoid installing a fixture \
                     whose breach targets would be missing at runtime. Single-threaded \
                     host invariant violated — investigate caller."
                );
                return;
            }
        }
```

