### Performance Optimization: Defer Wall Occlusion Calculation

Currently, `nearest_wall_stop` is called unconditionally on every tick the player fires, even if there are no targets in the broadphase candidate list. Since `nearest_wall_stop` iterates over the entire `DistrictWallList` (which contains up to 3,600 walls), this can lead to unnecessary CPU overhead when firing into empty space.

Moving the `nearest_wall_stop` calculation inside the `if let Some(...) = candidates.first()` block ensures that we only perform the wall-occlusion scan when there is actually a candidate target to check.

```suggestion
    if let Some(&(ray, _perp, target)) = candidates.first() {
        let wall_stop = nearest_wall_stop(player_pos, (aim.x, aim.y), walls.as_deref());
        // The nearest candidate is the hit unless a wall stops the ray
        // first; if it does, every farther candidate is behind it too, so
        // the shot hits the wall and nothing else.
        if ray <= wall_stop {
            events.write(DamageEvent {
                raw_amount: PISTOL_RAW_AMOUNT,
                damage_type: DamageType::Physical,
                target,
                impulse_magnitude: PISTOL_IMPULSE,
                impulse_direction: [aim.x, aim.y, 0.0],
                origin: *player_pos,
                source: Some(player_entity),
            });
        }
    }
```

